// === Vectorizer v2 — Legal -> Plan -> Execute auto-vectorizer (LLVM-class) ===
//
// This is the package entry point. It replaces the legacy pattern-matcher
// (opt_vec.cst) incrementally; until the cut-over (milestone M4/C17) it is gated
// behind d.vec_use_v2 and the legacy pass remains the default.
//
// Architecture (see ~/.claude/plans/vectorizer-llvm/MASTER-PLAN.md):
//   build CFG/dom (reuse cfg.cst/dom.cst) -> discover natural loops ->
//   for each innermost loop: LEGAL (mini-SCEV affine addresses + IV/recurrence
//   descriptors + dependence test) -> PLAN (VPlan-lite recipes + cost/VF/UF) ->
//   EXECUTE (splice widened SIMD IR + skeleton + runtime alias/ISA dispatch).
//
// Runs at codegen time (gen_func), -O2 only, post mid-end, before pass_unroll —
// the same seam the legacy pass uses. Returns 1 if it transformed a loop (the
// caller re-invokes to a fixpoint, <=16), 0 otherwise.
//
// M0/C1: scaffold only — pass_vectorize2 is a no-op (returns 0). The analysis
// spine (loop discovery, SCEV, descriptors, dependence) lands in C2-C5 with zero
// codegen risk; the first IR-emitting commit is M3/C13.

use "../defs.cst" as d;

fn pass_vectorize2(func as *d.IRFunction) as i32 {
    // M0 scaffold: no transformation yet.
    return 0;
}
